#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:8
msgid "SYNOPSIS: Setting up dosemu with freeDOS or any other DOS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:13
msgid ""
"DESCRIPTION: Sometimes you want to use the good old Disk Operating System, "
"e.g. for playing some real old games (like commander keen), but you don't "
"want to shutdown your linux box and don't have a DOS bootdisk anyway..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:16
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[ATTENTION: dosemu is discontinued in favour of dosbox (available on\n"
" http://dosbox.sourceforge.net) - but it's still faster in most cases!]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:19
msgid ""
"PREREQUISITES: http://dosemu.sf.net - dosemu-1.2.0.tgz, most actual "
"dosemu-freedos-bin.tgz"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:21
msgid "HINT:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"./configure --prefix=/usr --enable-experimental \\\n"
" --with-fdtarball=<wherever you stored dosemu-freedos-bin.tgz> &&\n"
"make &&\n"
"make install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:29
msgid ""
"If the installation breaks due to not finding bdftopcf, just use \"make "
"install\" again. The error shouldn't occur on the 2nd try."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:33
msgid ""
"now try \"dos\" or \"xdos\". If xdos complains about not finding the "
"necessary fonts, you should edit either your etc/X11/XftConfig or "
"/etc/fonts/fonts.conf (if you're using the newest X-Server with xft) and add "
"to the first lines"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:36
msgid ""
"'dir \"/usr/X11R6/lib/X11/fonts/misc\"' in XftConfig or "
"'<dir>/usr/X11R6/lib/X11/fonts/misc</dir>' in fonts.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:39
msgid ""
"if you're not using xft, you will have to restart the x server to let the "
"changes take effect or use the commands:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:42
msgid "xset +fp /usr/X11R6/lib/X11/fonts/misc xset fp rehash"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:44
msgid "and try to start dosemu again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:48
msgid ""
"If you did not use the freedos image, you will have to set up your dos image "
"yourself: make a directory /usr/share/dosemu and copy the io.sys and the "
"msdos.sys of your dos to this directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:54
msgid ""
"A minor problem is that the src/plugin/commands dir does not contain all of "
"the dosemu stuff, for example the cdrom.sys driver is missing. You'll find "
"the tasm sources in /src/commands. Since you propably don't have tasm, "
"you'll have to find a way to 1. extract that driver from the binary "
"distribution or 2. compile it without tasm using the gcc assembler:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:61
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cd src/commands &&\n"
"for i in aspi cdrom ems emufs; do\n"
"  as -o ${i}.sys < ${i}.S\n"
"done &&\n"
"mkdir /usr/share/dosemu/dosemu &&\n"
"cp *.sys /usr/share/dosemu/dosemu\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/dosemu.txt:63
msgid ""
"You may now start \"dosemu\" or \"xdosemu\" and install your DOS software at "
"will."
msgstr ""

